potential issues**\\n\\nI'm considering a possible issue with using Direct ObservationWebClientCustomizer without the WebClientObservationAutoConfiguration—maybe that's acceptable? I also think about the suggestion to modify only the test file, but I need to clarify what exactly needs to be adjusted there. It's important to ensure that these changes won’t impact other parts of the project unintentionally. Keeping everything organized and functional is key, so I’ll take a closer look at how best to approach this.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented comprehensive tests in:\n\n`tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-webclient/4.1.0-RC1/src/test/java/org_springframework_boot/spring_boot_webclient/Spring_boot_webclientTest.java`\n\nCovered:\n- Spring Boot auto-configuration discovery entries.\n- `WebClientAutoConfiguration` creating prototype `WebClient.Builder` beans.\n- Connector/customizer integration using an in-process JDK `HttpServer`.\n- `WebClientCodecCustomizer` applying Boot codec customizers.\n- `ObservationWebClientCustomizer` recording Micrometer observations.\n- `WebClientObservationAutoConfiguration` creating the observation customizer when an `ObservationRegistry` is available.\n\nNo build or test execution was performed, per instructions.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0d066e18265a3281016a3efb53c69481909a60e789e1a3d424\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 870, "output": 669, "cacheRead": 57856, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 59395, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782512455545, "responseId": "resp_0d066e18265a3281016a3efb48296081908e5c2224956c6e2d"}}
